This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as question generation and summarization, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of a mixture of experts, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a proxy for ground truth labels, which is a technique used in various subfields of computer science such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an encoder-decoder model, which is a common technique in computer vision and falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
